Commands that make your life easier when working with <code>git</code> on postmarketOS.

=== How do I fetch a pull request from GitHub? ===
<syntaxhighlight lang="shell">
git fetch origin pull/ID/head:BRANCHNAME
git checkout BRANCHNAME
</syntaxhighlight>

...where ID is the ID of the pull request, and BRANCHNAME is the name of the branch as you want it locally.
